just_use search.go

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Two-trip pattern: /api/v1/search returns lightweight ID tuples (no content,
no names); client calls /api/v1/hydrate with the IDs it wants. Keeps search
cheap and lets the client cache hydrated content separately.

BuildQuery is shared between the JSON API and the HTML search view so
filter semantics stay identical. Text search joins the message_fts virtual
table (trigram tokenization — any 3+ char substring matches, including URLs
and code, which is the advertised differentiator). Access filter is the
same public-or-subscribed check that messages.go uses.
